USA Cycling Beginning Race Program(BRP) p/b Rock N' Road
description:
New for this Year is the USAC Beginning Racer Program (BRP). The BRP Program is designed to provide new racers with an enjoyable and educational experience as they learn to race, the objective of the program is to inspire and educate new riders, increase annual licensed membership, and improve cycling skills, leading to safer and more enjoyable racing experiences. BRP is designed to be optional, fun, and valuable, leading to a desirable program, which, in turn, will lead to more rider participation.

The BRP is modeled off of the highly successful Northern California Early Bird Racing Series. Established approximately 30 years ago, the Early Bird Racing Series serves over 1,000 racers annually and is the culmination of many years of hard work from USA Cycling Coaches Larry Nolan, Laurel Green, Matt McNamara, John Cheetham, and Dan Smith.2016 BRP schedule at OC Great Park in Irvine:
course: Course is at the old El Toro Marine Air Station in Irvine Ca.  visit www.racegreatpark.com
registration:

June 2, 2016 – Cornering: choosing and holding your line – GPGP, Irvine, CA
June 30, 2016 – Pack awareness & skills – GPGP, Irvine, CA
June 16, 2016 – Sprinting basics – GPGP, Irvine, CA
June 23, 2016 – Bringing it all together – GPGP, Irvine, CA

description:

title: 2016-RED KITE OMNIUM EVENT #11 - THE BUMP CIRCUIT RACE- SUMMER
San Rafael Sunset Criterium
description:
Listen, this is criterium racing. This isn’t waiting for two hours to see guys pass in 10 seconds. This isn’t a TV commentator trying to add color to a grueling 8% grade climb through the Alps. This is “What the heck was that?” followed by “$#!* Here they come again!”

And for that lethargic forty seconds the riders are out of sight on the backside of the course, American cycling’s most renown voice and analyst, Dave Towle, is breaking down every nuance of what’s happening before your eyes.

And your blood is racing as local celebrity DJ Just pumps Afrojack and Pretty Lights through your veins...

And you have a beer in your hand. And a cowbell in the other...

This is a party. This is a nightclub on wheels, outdoors, under streetlights as dusk falls on an idyllic cityscape of Northern California in the summertime. This is one of the best annual events in all the Bay Area.

You don’t want to miss it.

Racing Classes for Pro Men and Women, Masters and USA Cycling Racing Categories plus 1 Mile foot race
course:

.8-mile in downtown San Rafael, CA
8% grade incline leading into turn 3 and decline into turn 4
fun and fast

description: C510 Super Cat III is a point to point bike adventure that will take riders to various locations over the east bay.  Riders will  be issued their first check point at the start point at Lake Merritt in Oakland.  The objective is to be the first one back to the finish after getting to all check points.  This is a fund raiser for the Alameda County Foodbank.  Registration fees are waived for riders raising at least $50 though online donations.  There will be prizes for the top finishers and top fund raisers.  We will provide food and beverages at the conclusion of the event.  More details on our websitehttp://www.crocker510.com/attorneys-1.html
course: This is a point to point event.  Riders will start at Lake Merritt and head to the first of 5 check points.  Expect about 60 miles of mostly road with the option to ride some fire roads to save milage.
registration: $20 for pre-registration.  $25 for on site or late registration.  Registration fees waived for riders raising $50 or more for the Alameda Country Food Bank.  See website for information about how to sign up for a virtual food drive:  http://www.crocker510.com/attorneys-1.html
directions:
Event start and finish is at bandstand area in Lakeside Park in Lake Merritt Oakland.  Lakeside Park is adjacent to Children's Fairyland.  Parking is available nearby.  Look for event signs.
